 @robertshiell887  It's as close as it should be. Stuntmen of Lee Major's generation would've come up in their careers making Westerns, like Cliff Booth in Tarantino's Once Upon A Time In Hollywood. That movie was set in 1969, and that whole part of Hollywood was dying off. By 1980 nobody was making Westerns in any major way.

In 2023, the world of Hollywood stuntwork is completely different. David Leitch, the director of this movie, worked as a stunt man like Colt Seavers. He was Brad Pitt's stunt double on several movies. He has over eighty credits for stuntwork, and not a single one is working on a Western. Lots of science fiction and action movies though.

Just as The Fall Guy tv series and its characters reflected the time the show was released and what life was like for stuntmen then, this movie and its versions of the characters reflects our time and what stuntwork is like for the people doing it for a living now.

